<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-390-804  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 390 804.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  June 26 1989 n544 p45(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A call for action: EDA leaders unite. (electronic designautomation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Costello, Joseph B.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Electronic design automation industry managers met at the annualDesign Automation Conference to consider the state of theindustry.andP;  Among the crucial trends are consolidation and themovement toward standardization of all EDA products.andP;  Such recentdevelopments as the Computer-Aided Design (CAD) Frameworkinitiative clearly indicate a desire on the part of customers forstandards that would help clear up the confusion resulting from amultitude of vendors and manufacturers extolling products in theirpursuit of market share.andP;  Only the establishment of industry-widestandards and the reduction of marketing hype can help the EDAindustry grow to the point where clients can confidently identify,purchase, modify and integrate tools from multiple vendors,creating an integrated EDA environment.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Design Automation ConferenceComputer-Aided DesignStandardizationAutomationMarket ShareManagementDesign.andO;Feature:   illustrationcartoon.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>